laboratory_examinations.findings: Appendix is borderline in size measuring 7.0 to 8.0 mm with potential hyperemia at the tip and trace fluid content. Minimal wall thickening involving the jejunum with mild mesenteric hyperemia possibly indicating mild jejunitis or early inflammatory changes. The visualized organs including liver, gallbladder, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, pancreas, and stomach are within normal limits. No free fluid or free air noted.
